Best #tricepsworkout & #bicepworkout 

1. Tricep Dips: Sit on the edge of a bench or chair, place your hands next to your hips, fingers facing forward. Slide your hips off the bench and lower your body by bending your elbows. Push back up to the starting position. Aim for 3 sets of 10-12 reps.

2. Bicep Curls: Stand with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing forward. Keep your elbows close to your sides and curl the weights up toward your shoulders. Slowly lower them back down. Perform 3 sets of 10-12 reps.

3. Tricep Pushdowns: Attach a rope or bar to a cable machine at chest height. Stand facing the machine, grab the attachment with an overhand grip, and position your elbows by your sides. Push the attachment downward until your arms are fully extended. Return to the starting position. Do 3 sets of 10-12 reps.

4. Hammer Curls: Hold a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing your torso. Keep your elbows close to your sides and curl the weights up, but this time, keep your palms facing your body throughout the movement. Slowly lower the weights back down. Perform 3 sets of 10-12 reps.

Remember to choose weights that challenge you but still allow you to maintain proper form. If you’re new to these exercises, consider consulting a fitness professional to ensure you’re performing them correctly.

1. Prioritize Strength Training: Incorporate resistance exercises like weightlifting, bodyweight exercises, or resistance band workouts into your routine 🏋🏾‍♂️ This helps build muscle, increase metabolism, and burn calories 🔥 even after your workout.

2. Consume a Balanced and Nutrient-Dense Diet: Focus on whole foods with a good balance of protein, carbohydrates, and healthy fats 🥑 Include lean protein sources like chicken, fish, tofu, or legumes, along with plenty of fruits 🍓, vegetables, and whole grains. Avoid processed and sugary foods as much as possible.

3. High-Intensity Interval Training (HIIT): Incorporate HIIT workouts into your training regimen 🏃🏽These short bursts of intense exercise followed by brief recovery periods help burn calories, boost metabolism, and promote muscle growth. Combine cardio exercises like sprints, jump rope, or cycling with bodyweight exercises for an effective workout 🚴
